To Start the data preparation 
Mandatory:
1. enter: java -jar data-preparation-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar -with-dependencies.jar 
2. add the scenario you want to prepare (multiple are possible): -s|--scenarios 6
	--> must be integer
3. add the CTU13 dataset-directory : -c|--ctu ../src/main/resources/TestCTU13/


Example:
Preparation/ Combination of scenarios 6,11,12:

java -jar data-preparation-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -s 6,11,12 --ctu ../src/main/resources/TestCTU13/

If Message "Arff files moved to: " is shown, means the data-preparation was successful

In the destination folder should now be a directory named:
scenarios=6,11,12_percentageTrain=80_separateTestScenario=false

Optional:

1. add the destination folder, in which the results are saved: -d|--destFolder 
	-> Default value: ../IDS/src/main/resources/
2. add percentage of the data for the training set: -p|--percentageTrain 
	-> Default value: 80
3. add number of folds for cross-validation: -f|--numOfFolds 
	-> Default value: 5
4. add the last number from the option -s as the test scenario: -t|--separateTestScenario 
	-> Default value: false
5. add -r true to remove all Background Instances: -r|--removeBackground 
	-> Default value: false

Example:
	Parameter:
	Preparation/ Combination of scenarios: 6,11,12
	Destination Folder: Default
	Percentage of data for training set: 50
	Number of folds for cross-validation: 6
	Separate Test Scenario: true
	Remove Background: Default
	
	Command line:
	java -jar data-preparation-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar -s 6,11,12 --ctu ../src/main/resources/TestCTU13/ -p 50 -f 6 --separateTestScenario
	
	java -jar data-preparation-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar 
	-s 6,11,12 
	--ctu ../src/main/resources/TestCTU13/ 
	-p 50 
	-f 6 
	--separateTestScenario
	
	
	In the destination folder should now be a directory named:
	scenarios=6,11,12_percentageTrain=50_separateTestScenario=true
	
	

WARNING:

Some combinations of scenarios may cause an "Out of Memory Error"
--> This my happen because of the file sizes of datasets

Currently working Datasets:
4,5,6,7,11,12